ed to rule fairly and (for a time at any rate) firmly. But in the latter part of his reign he paid more attention to his religion than to his kingdom. He died childless, and his death sparked off conflicting claims to his throne, which were resolved by the victory of William the Conqueror at the Battle of Hastings. His memory was honoured by Normans and English alike, for his fairness and his piety. Edward's mother was Norman; he had spent part of his youth in Normandy; and William claimed to have been nominated by Edward as his successor. Edward was canonized in the 12th century, and came to be venerated throughout Europe as a model of a Christian king."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Henry de Woodville was born about 1040, in Kerlouan, Finistère, Brittany, France. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1040–":"umbes 1040–Surnud","1060–Female":"1060–Surnud","1040–Male":"1040–Surnud","about 1040":"umbes 1040","1040":"1040","1060":"1060","Kerlouan, Finistère, Brittany, France":"Kerlouan, Finistère, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"about 1040–":"noin 1040–Kuollut","1060–Female":"1060–Kuollut","1040–Male":"1040–Kuollut","about 1040":"noin 1040","1040":"1040","1060":"1060","Kerlouan, Finistère, Brittany, France":"Kerlouan, Finistère, Bretagne, Ranska"},"fr":{"about 1040–":"environ 1040–Décédé","1060–Female":"1060–Décédée","1040–Male":"1040–Décédé","about 1040":"environ 1040","1040":"1040","1060":"1060","Kerlouan, Finistère, Brittany, France":"Kerlouan, Finistère, Bretagne, France","lifeSummary":"Henry de Woodville est né environ 1040, à Kerlouan, Finistère, Bretagne, France. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"about 1040–":"um 1040–Verstorben","1060–Female":"1060–Verstorben","1040–Male":"1040–Verstorben","about 1040":"um 1040","1040":"1040","1060":"1060","Kerlouan, Finistère, Brittany, France":"Kerlouan, Finistère, Bretagne, Frankreich","lifeSummary":"Henry de Woodville wurde um 1040 in Kerlouan, Finistère, Bretagne, Frankreich geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"abo